  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://slack.rook.io/).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\nIf a CR is created with an invalid type (e.g. string instead of int), the operator will continuously print errors to the log and will not be able to process other CRs of that type until the bad CR is deleted. \r\n\r\nFor example, when creating the CephBlockPool with replicated.size that is not a number, we see:\r\n```\r\nE0719 16:19:08.663569       6 reflector.go:126] github.com/rook/operator-kit/watcher.go:76: Failed to list *v1.CephBlockPool: v1.CephBlockPoolList.Items: []v1.CephBlockPool: v1.CephBlockPool.Spec: v1.PoolSpec.Replicated: v1.ReplicatedSpec.Size: readUint64: unexpected character: \ufffd, error found in #10 byte of ...|:{\"size\":\"badnumber\"|..., bigger context ...|null,\"failureDomain\":\"host\",\"replicated\":{\"size\":\"badnumber\"}}}],\"kind\":\"CephBlockPoolList\",\"metadat|...\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis can be fixed with CRD schema validation. We have some [CephCluster CR validation](https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/cluster/examples/kubernetes/ceph/common.yaml#L34-L84) already, we just need to add more validation to the other CRs, in particular where ints are required for pool count, etc.\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\nBetter handling of CR errors.\r\n",
